#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:8
msgid ""
"Since the `Chromium 142 update <https://developer.chrome.com/release-notes/"
"142>`_, using a self-signed certificate is no longer required. The "
"recommended approach is to use the :doc:`Local Network Access <pos_lna>` "
"method instead."
msgstr ""
"Depuis la `mise à jour Chromium 142 <https://developer.chrome.com/release-"
"notes/142>`_, l'utilisation d'un certificat auto-signé n'est plus requise. "
"L'approche recommandée consiste à utiliser la méthode :doc:`Accès réseau "
"local <pos_lna>` à la place."

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:12
msgid ""
"To work with Odoo, some printer models that can be used without an :doc:`IoT "
"system </applications/general/iot>` may require the HTTPS protocol to "
"establish a secure connection between the browser and the printer. However, "
"trying to reach the printer's IP address using HTTPS results in a warning "
"page in most web browsers. Force the connection to establish an HTTPS link "
"and enable the printer in Odoo."
msgstr ""
"Pour fonctionner avec Odoo, certains modèles d'imprimantes pouvant être "
"utilisés sans :doc:`système IoT </applications/general/iot>` peuvent "
"nécessiter le protocole HTTPS pour établir une connexion sécurisée entre le "
"navigateur et l'imprimante. Cependant, tenter d'accéder à l'adresse IP de "
"l'imprimante en utilisant HTTPS génère une page d'avertissement dans la "
"plupart des navigateurs web. Forcer la connexion pour établir un lien HTTPS "
"et activer l'imprimante dans Odoo."

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:21
msgid "Generation, export, and import of self-signed certificates"
msgstr "Génération, exportation et importation de certificats auto-signés"

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:23
msgid ""
"Printers that operate without an :doc:`IoT system </applications/general/"
"iot>` still require secure communication, which can be achieved "
"by :ref:`generating <pos/epos-ssc/certificate-generation>`, :ref:`exporting "
"<pos/epos-ssc/certificate-export>`, and/or :ref:`importing <pos/epos-ssc/"
"certificate-import>` a self-signed certificate."
msgstr ""
"Les imprimantes fonctionnant sans :doc:`système IoT </applications/general/"
"iot>` nécessitent toujours une communication sécurisée, qui peut être "
"obtenue en :ref:`générant <pos/epos-ssc/certificate-"
"generation>`, :ref:`exportant <pos/epos-ssc/certificate-export>` et/"
"ou :ref:`important <pos/epos-ssc/certificate-import>` un certificat auto-"
"signé."

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:29
msgid ""
"Generating a self-signed certificate should only be done **once**. Creating "
"another certificate causes devices using the previous one to lose HTTPS "
"access."
msgstr ""
"Générer un certificat auto-signé ne doit être effectué qu'**une seule "
"fois**. Créer un autre certificat entraîne la perte de l'accès HTTPS pour "
"les appareils utilisant le précédent."

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:31
msgid ""
"Printers that use an :doc:`IoT system </applications/general/iot>` do not "
"need a self-signed certificate, as the IoT box generates it automatically."
msgstr ""
"Les imprimantes utilisant un :doc:`système IoT </applications/general/iot>` "
"n'ont pas besoin de certificat auto-signé, car la box IoT le génère "
"automatiquement."

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:33
msgid ""
"For stable results, it is strongly recommended to use the Google Chrome "
"browser to generate the self-signed certificate."
msgstr ""
"Pour des résultats stables, il est fortement recommandé d'utiliser le "
"navigateur Google Chrome pour générer le certificat auto-signé."

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:37
msgid ""
"To export self-signed certificates from an operating system or a web browser "
"that is not mentioned in this documentation, search for `export SSL "
"certificate` and the name of your browser or operating system in the "
"preferred search engine. Similarly, to import self-signed certificates, "
"search for `import SSL certificate root authority` in the preferred search "
"engine."
msgstr ""
"Pour exporter des certificats auto-signés depuis un système d'exploitation "
"ou un navigateur web non mentionné dans cette documentation, rechercher "
"`export SSL certificate` et le nom du navigateur ou du système "
"d'exploitation dans le moteur de recherche préféré. De même, pour importer "
"des certificats auto-signés, rechercher `import SSL certificate root "
"authority` dans le moteur de recherche préféré."

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:45
msgid "Self-signed certificate generation"
msgstr "Génération de certificat auto-signé"

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:47
msgid ""
"The generation process depends on the :abbr:`OS (Operating System)` and the "
"browser."
msgstr ""
"Le processus de génération dépend du :abbr:`système d'exploitation` et du "
"navigateur."

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:51
#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:101
msgid "Windows 10 & Linux"
msgstr "Windows 10 et Linux"

#: ../../content/applications/sales/point_of_sale/hardware_network/epos_ssc.rst:53
